@baseUrl = http://localhost:5210
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Registrar usuário
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/session/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "john_doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123!"
}

###

### 2. Login (cria sessão)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/session/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "john_doe",
  "password": "SecurePass123!",
  "deviceName": "Chrome on Windows"
}

###

### 3. Login de outro dispositivo
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/session/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "john_doe",
  "password": "SecurePass123!",
  "deviceName": "Firefox on Linux"
}

###

### 4. Renovar tokens (refresh rotation)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/session/refresh
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "refreshToken": "COLE_O_REFRESH_TOKEN_AQUI"
}

###

### 5. Listar sessões ativas
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/session
Authorization: Bearer COLE_O_ACCESS_TOKEN_AQUI

###

### 6. Logout da sessão atual
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/session/logout
Authorization: Bearer COLE_O_ACCESS_TOKEN_AQUI

###

### 7. Revogar uma sessão específica por ID
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/session/COLE_O_SESSION_ID_AQUI
Authorization: Bearer COLE_O_ACCESS_TOKEN_AQUI
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "reason": "Dispositivo perdido"
}

###

### 8. Revogar todas as outras sessões (mantém a atual)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/session?keepCurrent=true
Authorization: Bearer COLE_O_ACCESS_TOKEN_AQUI

###

### 9. Revogar TODAS as sessões incluindo a atual
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/session?keepCurrent=false
Authorization: Bearer COLE_O_ACCESS_TOKEN_AQUI
